Colombian Stocks: Avianca Taca, Argos, Textiles Fabricato

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-12T16:27:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/colombian-stocks-avianca-taca-argos-textiles-fabricato.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:57 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index dropped 0.1 percent to 14,185.88, while the
Colcap Index fell 0.2 percent to 1,694.50.  Avianca Taca Holding SA (PFAVTA CB), owner of  Colombia ’s
biggest airline, gained 1.9 percent to 5,400 pesos in its second
day of trading.  Cementos Argos (CEMARGOS CB), Colombia’s biggest cement
maker, rose 0.7 percent to 10,880 pesos after buying assets with
an enterprise value of $760 million from Lafarge SA, the world’s
biggest cement producer, as the French company aims to regain an
investment-grade  credit rating .  Textiles Fabricato Tejicondor SA (FABRI)  , Colombia’s
biggest textile maker, gained 2.9 percent to 53.5 pesos, the
highest price since June 2007 on an intraday basis, after U.S.
Secretary of State  Hillary Clinton  said yesterday she sees
“great progress” toward concluding free trade agreements with
Panama and Colombia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
